about.summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in the console. The default summary statistics may be modified by the user as can the default formatting. Support for data frames and vectors is included, and users can implement their own skim methods for specific object types as described in a vignette. Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions for managing these on specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr" vignette and the README.

name: r-skimr
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "2.0.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-skimr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/skimr/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 93d2d4684423c737f965030d1436887f295836c87665c37bf0efd7f0ea73208c

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr
    - r-repr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=2.0.0
    - r-tidyr >=1.0
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.5
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr
    - r-repr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=2.0.0
    - r-tidyr >=1.0
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.5

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('skimr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('skimr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://docs.ropensci.org/skimr (website), https://github.com/ropensci/skimr
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in
    the console. The default summary statistics may be modified by the user as can the
    default formatting. Support for data frames and vectors is included, and users can
    implement their own skim methods for specific object types as described in a vignette.
    Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions for managing
    these on specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr" vignette and
    the README.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
